## Theory
Another type of allowed logical sources are SQL databases. When the data source is a SQL database, the mapping must specify that the dataType is ***rr:SQL2008***. Since tables use the row format, it behaves similarly to CSV files. In addition is not needed to provide an iterator.
```
<#TriplesMap> rml:logicalSource [ 
	    rml:source "databasePath";
	    rml:referenceFormulation rr:SQL2008 ;
	];
	rr:objectMap [ 
		rr:column "columnName"
	].
```
